{"favorite_id": 10128, "calc_type": "calculator", "dosing": false, "full_title_en": "Patient Activity Scale II (PAS II) for RA", "short_title_en": "Patient Activity Scale II for RA", "medium_description_en": "<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-9e1d7a17-7fff-d33c-586e-bd51d57d6edd\">Quantifies severity of rheumatoid arthritis (RA) using patient-reported symptoms.</span>", "short_description_en": "RA severity, less extensive than PAS.", "before_use": "", "instructions_en": "<p>Note: the PAS II is an alternative to the <calculator id=\"10127\">PAS</calculator>. PAS II uses a slightly different questionnaire with fewer questions than the original PAS, though the overall accuracy of the two is the same.</p>", "purpose_en": ["Prognosis"], "disease_en": ["Rheumatoid Arthritis"], "specialty_en": ["Rheumatology", "Orthopedics", "Primary Care", "Internal Medicine", "Hospitalist Medicine"], "chief_complaint_en": ["Joint Pain"], "system_en": ["Musculoskeletal", "Rheumatologic"], "search_abbreviation_en": ["Disease activity", "pain vas", "haq-II", "arthritis", "patient global health", "haq 2", "haq II", "haq2", "haqII"], "slug": "patient-activity-scale-ii-pas-ii-ra", "seo": {"meta_description_en": "The Patient Activity Scale (PAS) for RA quantifies severity of rheumatoid arthritis (RA) using patient-reported symptoms.", "keywords_en": "Disease activity, arthritis, patient global health, haq, pain vas"}, "content": {"how_to_use": {"use_case_en": "<p>Do you use the&nbsp;PAS II for RA and want to contribute your expertise?&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.mdcalc.com/join-us\" target=\"_blank\">Join</a>&nbsp;our contributor team!</p>", "pearls_pitfalls_en": "", "why_use_en": ""}, "next_steps": {"advice_en": "<p>Do you use the&nbsp;PAS II for RA and want to contribute your expertise?&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.mdcalc.com/join-us\" target=\"_blank\">Join</a>&nbsp;our contributor team!</p>", "management_en": "", "critical_actions_en": ""}, "about": {"formula_en": "<p dir=\"ltr\">PAS II = (A x 3.33 + B + C) / 3, where</p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A = Health Assessment Questionnaire Disability Index II&nbsp;(HAQ-II), calculated by&nbsp;averaging selected points from table below.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">B = Pain Visual Analog Scale (ask patient to rate pain on a scale of 0-10, where 10 is the worst pain imaginable).</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">C = Patient Global Assessment of Disease Activity (ask patient to rate how well they are doing in the past week considering all the ways their disease affects them on a scale of 0-10, where 10 is the worst).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p></p>\n<table><colgroup><col width=\"*\" /><col width=\"*\" /><col width=\"*\" /></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Variable</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Points</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"3\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Is the patient able to:</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"4\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Stand up from a straight chair</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Without any difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">0</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With some difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With much difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">2</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Unable</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">3</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"4\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Walk outdoors on flat ground</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Without any difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">0</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With some difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With much difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">2</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Unable</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">3</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"4\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Get on and off the toilet</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Without any difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">0</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With some difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With much difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">2</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Unable</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">3</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"4\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Reach and get down a 5-pound object (such as a bag of sugar) from just above&nbsp;the head</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Without any difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">0</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With some difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With much difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">2</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Unable</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">3</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"4\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Open car doors</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Without any difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">0</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With some difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With much difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">2</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Unable</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">3</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"4\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Do outside work (such as yard work)</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Without any difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">0</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With some difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With much difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">2</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Unable</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">3</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"4\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Wait in a line for 15 minutes</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Without any difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">0</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With some difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With much difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">2</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Unable</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">3</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"4\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Lift heavy objects</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Without any difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">0</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With some difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With much difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">2</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Unable</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">3</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"4\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Move heavy objects</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Without any difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">0</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With some difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With much difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">2</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Unable</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">3</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"4\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Go up 2 or more flights of stairs</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Without any difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">0</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With some difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With much difficulty</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">2</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Unable</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">3</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>", "more_info_en": "<p dir=\"ltr\">Interpretation:</p>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<table><colgroup><col width=\"*\" /><col width=\"*\" /></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>PAS II</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Disease activity</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">0.00-0.25</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remission</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">0.26-3.70</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Low/minimal</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">3.71-7.99</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Moderate</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">8.00-10.00</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">High/severe</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ddb71059-7fff-91e6-56c4-7328f8293f90\"></span><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ddb71059-7fff-91e6-56c4-7328f8293f90\"><br /></span></p>", "evidence_based_medicine_en": "", "references_list": {"Original/Primary Reference": [{"href": "http://www.jrheum.org/content/32/12/2410", "text": "Wolfe F, Michaud K, Pincus T. A composite disease activity scale for clinical practice, observational studies, and clinical trials: the patient activity scale (PAS/PAS-II). J Rheumatol. 2005;32(12):2410-5."}], "Other References": [{"href": "https://www.rheumatology.org/Portals/0/Files/Rheumatoid%20Arthritis%20Disease%20Activity%20Measures.pdf", "text": "Anderson J, Caplan L, Yazdany J, et al. Rheumatoid arthritis disease activity measures: American College of Rheumatology recommendations for use in clinical practice. Arthritis Care Res (Hoboken). 2012;64(5):640-7."}], "Validation": [{"href": "", "text": ""}], "Clinical Practice Guidelines": [{"href": "", "text": ""}], "Manufacturer Website": [{"href": "", "text": ""}], "Outcomes": [{"href": "", "text": ""}]}}, "contributor": {"expert_name": []}, "reviewer": {"expert_name": []}, "creator": [{"name": "Dr. Frederick Wolfe", "creator_info": {"about_en": "Frederick Wolfe, MD, is a rheumatologist and clinical professor of medicine at the University of Kansas School of Medicine. He is also the director of the National Data Bank for Rheumatic Disease. Dr. Wolfe\u2019s primary research is focused on outcomes of rheumatic diseases.", "photo_en": "htt